main event: A bright, round object was observed over Duluth AFB, Minnesota for approximately 1.5 hours on October 5, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared brighter and larger than a star, and changed color from red-orange to white.
The object seemed to slowly move up and down a little, and faded at dawn.
The object was observed by 2/Lt. Eric Olson, SSgt. Kickerbocker, and 5 other air police officers.
Small lights were seen at the same time and place as a SAC flare drop.
The object was estimated to be about one-eighth the size of the full moon.
witnesses: 2/Lt. Eric Olson, SSgt. Kickerbocker, and 5 other air police officers
